Researchers say widely-prescribed drugs could be contributing to obesity epidemic . 
  A third of 10-11 year olds and a fifth of 4-5 year olds in England are overweight . 
  Finnish researchers compared weight and height of 12,000 healthy two year olds . 
  By two years-old, one in five boys and one in ten girls was overweight or obese . 
  Children who had taken antibiotics as young babies were particularly likely to be overweight . 
 